args: Lord Seimei?! Lord Seimei, I'm here!
Huh? There ain't no one here.
I'm too late... Oh, what've I done?
Lady Mitsuhide? Gozu?\nWhat're y'all doin' here?
I just happened to run into Gozu Tenno,\nand when I told him you were planning an\nassault, he asked me to take him here.
Never thought we'd arrive to find Seimei\nabducted by the Mukuroshu.
It's all my fault—I went and ignored\nwhat he told me to do.
Yeah, I figure things would have played\nout differently if he'd come alone.
This is what happens when you try to do\nsomething that's beyond you by yourself.\nRight, Gozu Tenno?
Still, a subordinate's failing reflects on the\nboss—Seimei must have known this was\na distinct possibility.
And since our Wyrmclans are rivals for the\nposition of shogun, I've got no duty to\nhelp him out of this particular jam.
So if you've got nothing else to say,\nI'm going to take a nap and wait for\nall this to play out.
It's my responsibility, which means I gotta\nset things right by m'own self!
Okay, I said I wasn't going to get involved,\nbut I reeeally don't think Seimei wants you\nto feel that kind of obligation.
The last time you charged into danger like\na maniac, I asked if you could really\nhandle it all alone. Remember?
That's not something I would have said to\nSeimei, because I honestly think that guy\nis capable of anything he sets his mind to.
But YOU? You're a big ol' klutz and a half,\nand you really need to accept that.
Still, being a klutz doesn't mean there's\nnothing you can do in this situation.
Well, you're not helping me by being here,\nyou stupid fox!
Go find something even a useless idiot\nlike you can do—I'm counting on you.
...Yer right. I can't do nothin' on m'own,\n'cause I'm just a useless fox.
But Lord Seimei's countin' on me,\nand just 'cause I can't do nothin' on m'own\ndon't mean I can't do nothin' at all!
Please, Lady Mitsuhide!\nYa gotta help me save him! Ya just gotta!
Oh, fine. Why not? Having Seimei\nin my debt might even be fun.
You have my aid as well, for my intent\nwas to save Lord Seimei from the first.
Aw, yer both just the best!
So what's our first move? It doesn't look\nlike the enemy's been gone for very long.
Still, there's no guarantee we'll find\nanything useful just looking around,\nand I can't reeeally be bothered, so...
Lord Seimei is not the kind of person to\nlet himself be captured without a plan.
I am certain he will have left some\nmanner of clue to aid us.
All I see are a boatload of jufu\nscattered all over the floor.
Wait... I know how to find him!
See, I can detonate them jufu there and\nmake 'em stun enemies with bright light\nand crazy noise and the like.
Is that not the same skill you were\npracticing with Lord Seimei this morning?\nI recall it going...not well.
Look, just put that in the ol' dustbin.\nRight now, we gotta focus on the jufu\non the floor there.
I know I scattered more of 'em than that,\nwhich means Lord Seimei likely managed\nto grab a few before bein' hauled off.
And you think you can detonate them\nfrom afar to learn his location?
So long as they're somewhere my mana\ncan reach, yer sure as shootin' I can!
I can vouch for this; I was a victim\nof such just this morning.
Well, if you can do it, let's stop talking\nabout it and just get it done already.
We need to try it before the Mukuroshu\ntake Seimei and the jufu out of range.
So Gozu Tenno and I just go outside\nand listen for the detonation, right?
If this can lead us to Lord Seimei,\nI will gladly try. Let us be off.
*pant* *pant* I'm gonna show everyone\nthere ARE things I can do!
O that which shines like the darn sun!\nI beseech ya, release yer light'n make\nmanifest its brilliance! Onmyo! Haaaah!
*cough* *cough* Aw, horseshoes.\nI failed again. ...But I ain't givin' up!
Yeee-haw! I did it! It blowed up but good!\nNow we can find Lord Seimei!
Hang in there, Lord Seimei!\nI'll be there before you know it!
Judging by the direction of the sound\nand the faintly remaining smoke,\nLord Seimei should be in this area!
Knowing him, he's probably taken\nadvantage of the explosion to start\ncausing new trouble.
He always has to do everything himself!
Would you please cram it already?
Well, well. Look who finally showed up.\n...What'd you bring the lazy mouse for?
Oh, she insisted she wanted my help,\nand I thought it was a very nice chance\nto put you in my debt.
If you want me to feel like I owe you,\nyou'd better put the work in.
Nah, I'm good. I'm just gonna protect the\nlady over there while you do your thing.
*sigh* You are so hard to read.
I'll give that big one to you, Gozu Tenno.
You ready for a fight, Kuzunoha?
You were right about me all along, master.\nI ain't like you, and I ain't no help to\nnobody what when I'm by m'lonesome.
I know I caused more trouble'n a newborn\nbull in a surgery clinic, but I still wanna\nhelp ya if'n I can!
Heh. Then give it your best shot.
